steps.description:
Create a table with a Variant column:
```sql
SET allow_experimental_variant_type = 1;

CREATE TABLE test_variant (
    id UInt32,
    data Variant(String, UInt64, Array(String))
) ENGINE = MergeTree() ORDER BY id;

INSERT INTO test_variant VALUES
    (1, 'hello'), (2, 42), (3, ['a', 'b']);

SELECT id, data, variantType(data) FROM test_variant;
```

Test querying Variant columns:
```sql
SELECT * FROM test_variant WHERE variantType(data) = 'String';
SELECT data.String FROM test_variant;
```
Confirm type-specific access and filtering work correctly.
